## [2026-03-22 02:15:00 UTC] Phase 1: Foundation — Exceptions, Expanded Models, V2 URL

### Context
- Establish type system and error hierarchy that all subsequent phases build on

### Action Taken
- **`london_data_store/exceptions.py`** (NEW): Custom exception hierarchy — `LondonDataStoreError` base, `DatasetNotFoundError`, `FormatNotAvailableError` (both also subclass `ValueError` for backward compat), `DownloadError`, `CacheError`
- **`london_data_store/models.py`** (EXPANDED): Added 20+ fields to Dataset (`id`, `title`, `canonical`, `topics`, `licence_url`, `licence_title`, `contact`, `publisher`, `update_frequency`, `created_at`, `archived_at`, `sharing`, `webpage`, `geo`, `author`, `author_email`, `parent`, `team`), 8+ fields to Resource (`title`, `description`, `temporal_coverage_from/to`, `check_hash`, `check_size`, `check_http_status`, `check_mimetype`, `check_timestamp`), `is_archived` property, updated `from_api_dict()` to handle nested `licence` and `custom` objects
- **`london_data_store/api.py`**: Changed default URL to v2, replaced `ValueError` with custom exceptions
- **`london_data_store/__init__.py`**: Exported all exceptions
- **`tests/conftest.py`**: Enriched `SAMPLE_CATALOGUE` with all v2 fields
- **`tests/test_exceptions.py`** (NEW): 7 tests for exception hierarchy and backward compat
- **`tests/test_models.py`** (EXPANDED): Added 9 tests for v2 fields, `is_archived`, `from_api_dict` with nested licence/custom

### Outcome
- Success — all tests passing, foundation ready for subsequent phases

### Bugs / Errors Encountered
- Write tool "File has been modified since read" errors — had to Read files before Write
- Ruff UP017 (`timezone.utc` → `datetime.UTC`), F401, B905 — auto-fixed

### Fix or Mitigation
- Read-before-write pattern for all file modifications
- `ruff check . --fix` for auto-fixable issues, manual fix for B905 (`zip()` without `strict=`)

### Pitfalls & Future Risks
